<paragraph id="AA425C2ABF74FFC85A47FCA8343A4F65" blockId="25.[264,1324,847,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="98898038BF74FFC85A47FCA8372D4805" bold="true" box="[312,579,847,873]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">General distribution:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="1A955677BF74FFC85934FCA8343E4F65" country="Canada" location="Rocky Mountain region" municipality="southern Quebec" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Massachusetts">
This is a boreal species occurring across southern 
<collectingCountry id="D2EA1CBABF74FFC85FE0FCA831984805" box="[1183,1270,847,873]" name="Canada" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Canada</collectingCountry>
and the northern United States from 
<collectingMunicipality id="4A26C650BF74FFC859DBFC90361F48FD" box="[676,881,887,913]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">southern Quebec</collectingMunicipality>
and eastern 
<collectingRegion id="683992C8BF74FFC85F66FC9031AC48FD" box="[1049,1218,887,913]" country="United States of America" name="Massachusetts" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Massachusetts</collectingRegion>
west to British Columbia and southern 
<collectingRegion id="683992C8BF74FFC85906FC78366648D5" box="[633,776,927,953]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Washington</collectingRegion>
. In the 
<location id="AF220AF1BF74FFC85821FC78311948D5" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:2254ED3CBF75FFC85A77FA3637194F35:AF220AF1BF74FFC85821FC78311948D5" box="[862,1143,927,953]" country="Canada" municipality="southern Quebec" name="Rocky Mountain region" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" stateProvince="Massachusetts">Rocky Mountain region</location>
it occurs as far south as northern 
<collectingRegion id="683992C8BF74FFC85A90FC2037FC488D" box="[495,658,967,993]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
, northeastern 
<collectingRegion id="683992C8BF74FFC8583BFC2036CB488D" box="[836,933,967,993]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Arizona</collectingRegion>
, and central 
<collectingRegion id="683992C8BF74FFC85F2FFC2031FD488D" box="[1104,1171,967,993]" country="United States of America" name="Idaho" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Idaho</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CE6C21DBBF74FFC85FD5FC2034294F65" author="Lafontaine, J. D." pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref23111" refString="Lafontaine, J. D. (1987) Noctuoidea, Noctuidae (part): Noctuinae, Euxoa. In: Hodges, R. W., Davis, D. R., Dominick, T., Ferguson, D. C., Franclemont, J. G., Munroe, E. G., &amp; Powell, J. A. (Eds.) The Moths of America North of Mexico, fasc. 25.2, Allen Press, Lawrence, Kansas. 237 pp." type="book" year="1987">Lafontaine 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AA425C2ABF74FFC85A47FBF037194F35" blockId="25.[264,1324,847,1113]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
